description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for x2 band 5 mental health nurse to join our team. You will need to be enthusiastic, motivated, dynamic and forward thinking. Evidence based practice and innovative therapies are encouraged. You need to have a commitment to maintaining and improving service user focused services to the highest standards. Your ability to communicate with service users, families and the public must be of the highest standards, and must have an ability to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team. A genuine interest in working with older adult with acute mental illness and potentially some physical health needs issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here on Orchard Ward we aim to offer a world class service through patient led care alongside the involvement and support from family and friends. We are looking for caring, supportive individuals who have the ambition and ability to think outside the box and practice with innovation. Whether you&#39;re experienced or newly qualified we want to hear from you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Just some of the benefits from working with us:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;1) flexible working, short time or full time contract&lt;br /&gt;2) A lifestyle not a job&lt;br /&gt;3) Training provided by experienced leaders &lt;br /&gt;4) An environment where you are free to challenge and suggest&lt;br /&gt;5) Hard to recruit supplement&lt;br /&gt;6) Free parking&lt;br /&gt;7) Perceptorship for newly qualified&lt;br /&gt;8) Development programmes&lt;br /&gt;9) Time to learn and developYou will be supported with training and development, and there is a robust supervision and appraisal system in place to assist with this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers a Golden Hello, or a Relocation package up to a maximum of £2000. (pro rata applies and subject to terms and conditions. Please see attached Protocol document).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to visit or for any further information about this post please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris Ikpeh on 01243 791836&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
